DOCSENDGO ADMIN PANEL SETUP
===========================
Admin URL after deployment:
https://YOUR-VERCEL-DOMAIN/232admin.html

IMPORTANT: 232admin.html is hidden from the normal website menu, but the URL itself is not a security boundary. Firebase Authentication + Firestore rules provide the security.

1) Firebase Console > Authentication > Sign-in method > enable Email/Password.
2) Authentication > Users > Add user. Use your Indus Appstore/developer email and a strong password.
3) Copy that user's UID.
4) Firestore Database > Start collection: admins
   Document ID: paste the UID
   Fields:
     active = true (Boolean)
     role = superadmin (String)
     email = your email (String)
5) Publish the included firestore.rules and storage.rules in Firebase Console.
6) Deploy all project files to Vercel.
7) Open /232admin.html and log in.

Admin features included:
- Dashboard counts
- User search, block/unblock and delete
- Receiver-file and share-code list/delete
- Admin announcements
- Maintenance mode, uploads and tools controls

NOTE:
The current user website does not yet read appConfig/adminNotifications for every feature. The Admin Panel stores these controls correctly in Firestore; the public app can be connected to them in a later update without changing the Admin Panel.
